The three corresponding new sails were now bent and reefed, and a storm-trysail 
was set further aft; so that the ship soon went through the water with some 
precision again; and the course—for the present, East-south-east—which he 
was to steer, if practicable, was once more given to the helmsman. For during 
the violence of the gale, he had only steered according to its vicissitudes. 
